ive, engaging the senses and the mind alike, conveys a deep appreciation of two incomparable winegrowing cultures, united despite their differences by a common ambition to produce the best wines in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aViticulturexFrancexBordeaux (Aquitaine). 0aViticulturexFrancexBurgundyxFrancexBordeaux (Aquitaine)xFrancexBurgundy. 0aViticulturezFrancezBordeaux (Aquitaine). 0aViticulturezFrancezBurgundy. 0aWine and wine makingxHistoryxFrancexBordeaux (Aquitaine). 0aWine and wine makingxHistoryxFrancexBurgundy. 0aWine and wine makingzFrancezBordeaux (Aquitaine)xHistory. 0aWine and wine makingzFrancezBurgundyxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520933316423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520933316.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles